# Lab 6B – Create systemd Timer

1. Create one-shot service
   vi /etc/systemd/system/daemon-workload-once.service

2. Create timer unit
   vi /etc/systemd/system/daemon-workload.timer

3. Reload systemd
   systemctl daemon-reload

4. Enable and start timer
   systemctl enable --now daemon-workload.timer

5. Verify timer
   systemctl list-timers

6. Verify execution logs
   journalctl -u daemon-workload-once.service
